<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<minf expander="minf_2.0">
<d>
  <d name="en">
    <xhtml name="short">Compute (diffusion) Orientation Distribution (ODF) from a diffusion tensor model</xhtml>
    <d name="parameters">
        <xhtml name="tensor_coefficients">Estimated coefficients of a diffusion tensor. If no instance already exist and that you want to generate an ODF from tensor
        please use <a href="bvprocess://DTI_fitting"><bvProcessName name="DTI_fitting"/></a> or <a href="bvprocess://DTIReconstructionPipeline"><bvProcessName name="DTIReconstructionPipeline"/></a></xhtml>
        <xhtml name="tensor_model">Diffusion tensor model parameters</xhtml>
        <xhtml name="sphere">Sample sphere where to evaluate the ODF. For visualisation purpose, the finer the better but may create memory problem.</xhtml>
        <xhtml name="mask"> Region of interest to restrain the ODF computation. Does not have to be a binary volume</xhtml>
        <xhtml name="d-odf"> Diffusion Orientation Distribution on the sphere: radial probability of diffusion.</xhtml>
    </d>
      <xhtml name="long"> Compute (diffusion) Orientation Distribution (ODF) from a diffusion tensor model.</xhtml>
  </d>
</d>
</minf>
